  "prompt": "What does Accent do to food?",
  "response": "Accent is a brand name for a seasoning product that contains monosodium glutamate (MSG). When added to food, Accent enhances the savory, umami flavor of dishes. It is commonly used in small amounts to boost the overall taste of various recipes, including soups, stews, meats, and vegetables. Some people find that it helps to bring out the natural flavors of the ingredients in a dish. However, it's worth noting that some individuals may be sensitive to MSG and experience symptoms like headaches or nausea after consuming it.",
